							Chocolate Buttercream Frosting (recipe below) 						</li>
												<li data-ingredient-index="2" data-ingredient-id="156295">
							28 Gummy Worms (original or sour) 						</li>
												<li data-ingredient-index="3" data-ingredient-id="156296">
							18 Oreo Cookies, crushed ~ 6-8 Tbsp						</li>
										</ul>
			</div>
				</div>
		<div class="mv-create-hands-free"></div>
		<div class="mv-create-instructions mv-create-instructions-slot-v2">
		<h3 class="mv-create-instructions-title mv-create-title-secondary">Instructions</h3>
		<ol><li data-step-index="0" id="mv_create_1578_1">First, prepare and bake the chocolate cupcakes. You will need to let them fully cool before frosting.</li><li data-step-index="1" id="mv_create_1578_2">Next, put the Oreo™ cookies into a plastic bag and crush them into very fine pieces. You can use the back of a spoon to get any clumps. Note: remove the frosting from inside the cookies or leave it - both ways work.</li><li data-step-index="2" id="mv_create_1578_3">Make the chocolate frosting or scoop tub frosting into a piping bag or plastic zip top bag. Add a swirl of chocolate frosting to the top of each cupcake - remember, it doesn't have to be pretty, as we will be covering most of it.</li><li data-step-index="3" id="mv_create_1578_4">Spoon the crushed Oreo™ cookies onto the frosting of each cake. Use as little or as much as you like but start with each getting 2-3 teaspoons to add to the overall look.</li><li data-step-index="4" id="mv_create_1578_5">Cut a few of the worms into smaller pieces (halves or thirds). Add one full worm and a partial worm to each cupcake.</li></ol><p>ADDITIONAL RECIPES:</p><p>- <a href="https://rufflesandrainboots.com/lazy-girl-chocolate-cupcake-recipe/" target="_blank"><u>Easy Chocolate Cupcake Recipe </u></a></p><p>- <a href="https://rufflesandrainboots.com/easy-chocolate-buttercream-frosting-recipe/" target="_blank"><u>Chocolate Buttercream Frosting Recipe</u></a></p>	</div>
	<div class="mv-create-notes mv-create-notes-slot-v2">
		<h3 class="mv-create-notes-title mv-create-title-secondary">Notes</h3>
		<div class="mv-create-notes-content">
			<p><p>If making these using premade cupcakes and frosting, you will be done in 15 minutes.</p><p>If making these from scratch, plan on at least 1 hour and 15 minutes. While the cupcakes are baking, make the frosting to save on time, but remember to fully cool the cupcakes before frosting (can be put in the refrigerator). </p><p>Cupcakes and frosting can be made up to two days ahead. Store pre-frosted cupcakes on counter in an airtight container. Store frosting in the refrigerator in an air tight container.</p><p>Display ideas for a garden party, Halloween, nature / camping party, and a construction party are shared in the original recipe here: <a href="https://rufflesandrainboots.com/?p=71567">https://rufflesandrainboots.com/dirt-and-worms-cupcakes/</a></p></p>
		</div>
	</div>
<div class="mv-create-nutrition">
	<div class="mv-create-nutrition-box">
		<h4 class="mv-create-nutrition-title mv-create-strong"><span>Nutrition Information:</span></h4>

					<span class="mv-create-nutrition-item mv-create-nutrition-yield"><h4 class="mv-create-nutrition-label mv-create-uppercase mv-create-strong">Yield:</h4> 12</span>
		
					<span class="mv-create-nutrition-item mv-create-nutrition-serving-size "><h4 class="mv-create-nutrition-label mv-create-uppercase mv-create-strong">Serving Size:</h4> 1</span>
		
		<br><span class="mv-create-nutrition-amount"><em>Amount Per Serving:</em></span>

